`ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'requests'` — the `requests` package isn't installed in the Kudu shell environment. But more importantly this tells us the function app itself may also be missing packages.

**Run this in Kudu:**
```
python3 -m pip install requests azure-ai-inference azure-core --target /home/site/wwwroot/.python_packages/lib/site-packages
```

Then restart the function app from the portal and test from Postman again.

This installs the packages into the correct location that Azure Functions uses at runtime.
